Parliament, Friday, 26 June 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Justice and Correctional Services will later today receive progress report on the investigations by the Special Investigating Unit (SIU) into the matters referred to it concerning the Department of Justice and Constitutional Development, and will also receive a briefing on the mechanisms in place to facilitate cooperation between the SIU and the National Prosecuting Authority.
	
	In the evening the committee will receive a briefing on the operationalisation of the Protection of Information Act and capacitation/resourcing of the Information Regulator; on the preparation for the transfer of Promotion of Access to Information Act powers and functions to the information Regulator.
	
	Details of meetings are as follows:
	Date: 26 June 2020
	Time: 15:00
	
	Parliamentary Committees are open to the media and the public. Journalists wishing to cover these (including receiving links to virtual meetings) should send their cellphone numbers to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communications Services WhatsApp Group, where such information is shared. Journalists must send these requests using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow sittings live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
